body:
### Actual behaviour
- Owncloud does not notice changes to a local file without forcing a manual sync.
- On manual sync, a newer local file is overwritten by an older remote version.
### Expected behaviour
- Changes to a local file are automatically uploaded to the server.
- If this is not possible (eg, because background data is restricted), a manual sync should upload the newer version.
### Steps to reproduce
1. Sync a file that resides in the owncloud folder (eg. todo.txt)
2. Wait for sync to stop working. I don't know what conditions trigger this besides time. I suspect it's related to #1664.
3. Modify the file locally
   - Notice that changes are no longer automatically uploaded.
4. Open owncloud app, trigger manual sync
   - Notice that your local changes have been reverted to the previous state.

Can this problem be reproduced with the official owncloud server? Didn't test since it takes time and I use owncloud & my todo app regularly.
### Environment data

Android version: 5.0.1

Device model: sch-i545 (verizon galaxy s4)

Stock or customized system: rooted, deodexed, xposed, but still stock touchwiz.

ownCloud app version: 2.0.0 fdroid

ownCloud server version: 9.0.2
### Logs
#### Web server error log

A missing favicon.ico. Nothing relevant.
#### ownCloud log (data/owncloud.log)

Preface: I don't know that this will be useful at all, because there's plenty of unrelated issues. Note that this issue only started happening on upgrade of the client to 2.0.0 so I don't believe my server is the issue, despite errors.

